{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2016}} {{Infobox officeholder | honorific-prefix = | name = Deborah Lambkin | image_size = | caption = | parents = |birth_name = | birth_date = 1970 | birth_place = Ireland | death_date = | death_place = }} '''Deborah Lambkin''' is an Irish botanical artist who has been the official Orchid artist for the [[Royal Horticultural Society]].
== Career == Deborah Lambkin was born in 1970 and trained in the [[National College of Art and Design]]. She spent a number of years living in [[Dublin]] and working as an artist. She worked for Motive Advertising and Design which she left in 1998 to focus on her own art. She then moved to London where she began working for the [[Royal Horticultural Society]]'s Orchid committee in 2005 as the official artist. She has been commissioned to create the art for a number of magazines including [[Curtis's Botanical Magazine]], books and exhibitions.<ref name="Irishbotanicalartists">{{cite web |url=http://www.irishbotanicalartists.ie/event/an-evening-with-deborah-lambkin/ |title=An Evening with Deborah Lambkin – The Irish Society of Botanical Artists |newspaper=Irishbotanicalartists |date= |author= |accessdate= 12 October 2016}}</ref><ref name="RHS">{{cite web |url=https://www.rhs.org.uk/about-the-rhs/pdfs/publications/lindley-library-occasional-papers/volume-2-march-2010 |title=RHS: lindley library occasional papers |newspaper=RHS Organisation: |date= |author= |accessdate= 12 October 2016}}</ref><ref name="Irishtimes">{{cite web |url=http://www.irishtimes.com/news/beauty-at-a-brush-stroke-1.188022 |title=Beauty at a brush stroke |newspaper=Irishtimes |date=22 May 1999 |author=Jane Powers |accessdate= 12 October 2016}}</ref><ref name="Botanical">{{cite web |url=http://www.botanicalartandartists.com/botanical-artists-in-europe.html |title=Botanical Artists in Europe – Botanical Art & Artists |newspaper=Botanicalartandartists.com |date= |author= |accessdate= 12 October 2016}}</ref><ref name="Online">{{cite journal |url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/curt.12098/pdf |title=CONTRIBUTORS – 2015 – Curtis's Botanical Magazine – Wiley Online Library |date= |author= |accessdate= 12 October 2016 |doi=10.1111/curt.12098 |volume=32 |journal=Curtis's Botanical Magazine |page=91}}</ref><ref name="RHS press">{{cite web |url=http://press.rhs.org.uk/RHS-Gardens/Press-releases/An-Explosion-of-Colour-at-RHS-Garden-Wisley.aspx |title=Royal Horticultural Society – An Explosion of Colour at RHS Garden Wisley |newspaper=Press.rhs.org |date= |author= |accessdate= 12 October 2016}}</ref><ref name="Irish Orchids">{{cite web |url=http://www.irishorchidsociety.org/artists.php |title=Irish Orchid Society |newspaper=Irishorchidsociety.org |date= |author= |accessdate= 12 October 2016}}</ref>
She is one of only two Irish artists to win a gold medal at the RHS exhibition, the other being [[Wendy F. Walsh]].<ref name="Irishtimes"/> Her work is on display in the National Trust.<ref name="Nationaltrustcollections">{{cite web |url=http://www.nationaltrustcollections.org.uk/object/226214 |title=Drawing 226214 |newspaper=Nationaltrustcollections.org |date= |author= |accessdate= 12 October 2016}}</ref>
==Awards, Exhibitions and books== * 1998 RHS Grenfell Silver medal. * 1999 gold medal for her collection of eight paintings of nerines at the February's Winter Series Exhibition at the Royal Horticultural Society in London. * 2014 World Orchid Conference Botanical Art Exhibition<ref name="Botanical"/> * 2002. E. C. Nelson et alii ''The virtues of herbs of Master Jon Gardener''. Dublin: Strawberry Tree.
