{{Infobox artwork | image_file = Van Gogh - Blühender Obstgarten mit Blick auf Arles.jpeg | painting_alignment = | image_size = 300px | title = View of Arles, flowering orchards | alt = View of Arles, flowering orchards | other_language_1 = Original title, in French | other_title_1 = Vue d'Arles, vergers en fleurs | other_language_2 = Title in German | other_title_2 = Blick auf Arles, blühende obstgärten | artist = Vincent van Gogh | year = 1889 | catalogue = {{Flatlist}} *[[Jacob Baart de la Faille|F516]] *[[Jan Hulsker|JH1685]] {{Endflatlist}} | medium = oil on canvas | height_metric = 72 | width_metric = 92 | height_imperial = 28.3 | width_imperial = 36.2 | metric_unit = cm | imperial_unit = in | city = Munich | museum = [[Neue Pinakothek]] }}
'''''View of Arles, Flowering Orchards''''' is a painting by [[Vincent van Gogh]], executed in spring 1889, one of several paintings he produced in his [[Flowering Orchards (Van Gogh series)|''Flowering Orchards'' series]] while living in [[Arles]].
==Description== It supplies a view across a canal and the poplars on its board towards the historical center of Arles, with the towers of [[Church of St. Trophime|Saint-Trophime]] and College St Charles to the left, contrasted by recent building of the Caserne Calvin, housing the [[Zouave]] Regiment, to the right.<ref>{{cite book | title=Décoration: Vincent van Gogh's Werkreihe für das Gelbe Haus in Arles | author=Dorn, R | publisher=Georg Olms Verlag | location=Hildesheim, Zürich & New York | year=1990 | pages=469–470| isbn=3-487-09098-8 | url= }}</ref>
Van Gogh was acquainted with several of the Zouave officers, painted one in native uniform, and his portrait of Lieutenant Milliet is known as The Lover.<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2016-12-23|title=Portraits by Vincent van Gogh|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portraits_by_Vincent_van_Gogh&oldid=756285498|journal=Wikipedia|language=en}}</ref>
Poplar trees still stand along the canal, today, but the orchards and the Caserne are gone.
==Displays== Van Gogh incorporated this painting in his [[Vincent van Gogh's display at Les XX, 1890|selection]] of works to be displayed at [[Les XX]], in Bruxelles 1890.
